summary: TL* TAKATA RECALL. THE CONTACT OWNS A 2011 TOYOTA COROLLA. THE CONTACT RECEIVED NOTIFICATION OF NHTSA CAMPAIGN NUMBER: 16V340000 (AIR BAGS); HOWEVER, THE PART FOR THE RECALL REPAIR WAS UNAVAILABLE. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE MANUFACTURER EXCEEDED A REASONABLE AMOUNT OF TIME FOR THE RECALL REPAIR. WHILE DRIVING APPROXIMATELY 50 MPH, THE VEHICLE CRASHED INTO A DEER. THERE WERE NO INJURIES AND A POLICE REPORT WAS NOT FILED. THE FRONT BUMPER AND GRILL DETACHED FROM THE VEHICLE. THE AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY. THE BODY DAMAGE WAS REPAIRED AT SUTTLE AUTO REPAIR SHOP. THE CONTACT CALLED THE GLOUCESTER TOYOTA DEALER WHO STATED THAT THERE WERE NO PARTS AVAILABLE. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT MADE AWARE OF THE ISSUE. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 165,000. VIN TOOL CONFIRMS PARTS NOT AVAILABLE.
